title: Sansa in 8.03
body:
The promotional stills for 8.03 are out and they are probably out of order (that seems likely) but the one of Sansa sitting has my attention. She’s sitting alone with people in the background and watching something or someone. 

During the battle I don’t think she’s going to sit. And we’re not likely to see a lot of pre-battle imagery (there isn’t the time). So it’s most likely that this comes toward the end.

If it comes in the opening minutes of 8.03 she’s likely watching Theon and Bran leave, worried that they’re going to die. It could be her watching Dany and Jon leave, but I doubt it, she looks resigned and sad. As much as we like to consider her possible relationship with Jon, she doesn’t look at him like that. She’s hopeful around Jon, and sometimes even Dany.

And it really doesn’t make sense for any of the defenders of Winterfell to stand around smiling. 

But if this scene comes later? After Sansa is removed from the battle?

What would Sansa do to protect Winterfell? ANYTHING.

Time and again Sansa has proved she will do whatever it takes to survive and protect her lands and people. That would include going with the Golden Company or letting them take her if she thought it would save other people. 

There’s a few reason she might go to King’s Landing:
1) Kidnapped by Cersei - this one is a bit obvious and has been hinted at several times. 

2) To make an uneasy alliance - she won’t ever trust Cersei but if Sansa thought Dany and Jon were lost in battle? If she could trade herself for the Golden Company’s support? If Dany or Jon went mad? She’d work with Cersei.

3) To save someone else - if the Golden Company told her they would take her or Arya, her or Jon, or shoot Dany if she didn’t come… Sansa would go with them. She would do it because she knows she can survive Cersei and because she knows Winterfell needs defenders. She might even do it to save Tyrion or Jaime (although that seems like a stretch). 


The only other thing I can think is this is Sansa watching the bodies of the dead burn between the first attack and the second. 


So… thoughts? 

What is Sansa looking at?

summary: There are a lot of different ships with Sansa and I don't really care about most of them. Except for Theon, who surprisingly is...
body:
There are a lot of different ships with Sansa and I don’t really care about most of them. Except for Theon, who surprisingly is growing on me.

I don’t care with whom Sansa ends up with, if she even ends up with someone at all, I just want her to be happy.

After everything she went through, she deserves to be happy. I hope she is alive and happy by the end of the series.
